WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:03.733 --> 00:00:11.733
Proper subs by [mlnl]

2
00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:19.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

3
00:00:55.160 --> 00:00:57.036
Whoever gets to the temple first win!

4
00:00:57.061 --> 00:01:00.294
- What?
- Aang. no fair!

5
00:01:01.011 --> 00:01:02.100
Let's get him!

6
00:01:02.125 --> 00:01:03.125
Cmon hurry up!

7
00:01:12.265 --> 00:01:15.765
Hi. Nima. Good morning. Aang.
Hey Mipmip Oh. hello. Aang.

8
00:01:22.081 --> 00:01:24.080
Oh. perfect timing.

9
00:01:24.946 --> 00:01:26.080
Mind giving me a lift.

10
00:01:26.081 --> 00:01:27.979
Gyatso. this isn't the best time.

11
00:01:28.263 --> 00:01:30.080
I'm getting old. you know.

12
00:01:30.081 --> 00:01:32.100
My body doesn't move like it used to.

13
00:01:32.101 --> 00:01:34.120
I'm kind of in the middle of something.

14
00:01:34.606 --> 00:01:35.928
You are so heavy.

15
00:01:36.139 --> 00:01:37.536
Heavy? Me?

16
00:01:37.561 --> 00:01:39.100
I eat nothing but vegetables.

17
00:01:39.249 --> 00:01:41.100
Pie is not a vegetable.

18
00:01:41.125 --> 00:01:42.625
I'm gonna lose the race.

19
00:01:42.979 --> 00:01:44.100
Race? What race?

20
00:01:45.252 --> 00:01:48.100
- We finally won!
- We won! We won!

21
00:01:53.341 --> 00:01:54.961
Aang

22
00:01:54.985 --> 00:01:59.407
As an airbender. it's important
that you know when to show restraint.

23
00:02:00.343 --> 00:02:04.829
Even if you have the power
to win. you are the Avatar.

24
00:02:04.854 --> 00:02:09.362
A lot of people are going to rely on you.

25
00:02:19.201 --> 00:02:20.466
Where is the Avatar?

26
00:02:20.490 --> 00:02:22.140
- He's gone!
- He ran away!

27
00:02:22.141 --> 00:02:24.140
What? I'm here!

28
00:02:24.873 --> 00:02:26.140
Where's the Avatar?

29
00:02:26.141 --> 00:02:27.141
Avatar!

30
00:02:27.317 --> 00:02:29.140
Aang. where are you?

31
00:02:30.073 --> 00:02:32.187
Gyatso. I'm here!

32
00:02:34.942 --> 00:02:37.160
I'm right here!

33
00:02:37.161 --> 00:02:38.313
I'm here!

34
00:02:39.380 --> 00:02:40.646
Here!

35
00:02:41.161 --> 00:02:42.161
I'm here.

36
00:02:46.783 --> 00:02:48.160
Hey. Momo.

37
00:02:49.010 --> 00:02:50.160
Hi. Appa.

38
00:02:50.260 --> 00:02:52.824
- Was I asleep for long?
- Ooh! Okay. okay.

39
00:02:52.849 --> 00:02:54.180
I'm awake already.

40
00:02:54.181 --> 00:02:55.181
I know. I know.

41
00:02:55.229 --> 00:02:56.979
We've got a job to finish.

42
00:02:58.380 --> 00:03:00.180
Let's continue our journey.

43
00:03:00.555 --> 00:03:02.180
Back to our old home.

44
00:03:49.670 --> 00:03:51.220
This may not have been our best trip.

45
00:03:51.620 --> 00:03:54.240
but any Airbender relic we
find makes it all worthwhile.

46
00:04:00.245 --> 00:04:02.667
This could be the oldest
piece in our collection.

47
00:04:08.262 --> 00:04:09.711
Sonam.

48
00:04:21.261 --> 00:04:24.160
I miss you.

49
00:04:30.308 --> 00:04:32.708
Momo. go outside with Appa.

50
00:04:34.152 --> 00:04:35.255
Now!

51
00:04:43.440 --> 00:04:45.301
Who are you?

52
00:04:45.326 --> 00:04:46.718
Why are you doing this?

53
00:04:50.491 --> 00:04:51.785
Please Stop.

54
00:04:51.851 --> 00:04:53.280
I don't want to hurt you.

55
00:04:56.715 --> 00:04:59.300
- Where is it?
- No. that's not it.

56
00:04:59.301 --> 00:05:01.300
Hey. those are antiques.

57
00:05:12.583 --> 00:05:13.583
Enough!

58
00:05:17.246 --> 00:05:19.227
- Wait!
- I found it!

59
00:05:21.587 --> 00:05:23.586
Sonam. why an after you?

60
00:05:42.671 --> 00:05:43.671
Wait!

61
00:05:46.761 --> 00:05:48.934
No. that's 1.000 years old!

62
00:05:53.882 --> 00:05:54.790
Give it to me!

63
00:05:54.815 --> 00:05:56.659
Why don't we just talk? Maybe I can help.

64
00:05:56.684 --> 00:05:59.062
We don't need your help. Avatar.

65
00:05:59.361 --> 00:06:03.360
We're done living in a world where benders
have all the power and we have none.

66
00:06:03.361 --> 00:06:04.360
Who are you?

67
00:06:04.361 --> 00:06:05.590
We're the Denied.

68
00:06:05.635 --> 00:06:06.635
The Denied?

69
00:06:07.257 --> 00:06:08.360
Just kill him already!

70
00:06:08.361 --> 00:06:10.360
No! He'll bring the whole place down!

71
00:06:37.033 --> 00:06:38.633
You saved me.

72
00:06:40.967 --> 00:06:43.400
Kallik. grab the map! Let's go!

73
00:06:57.366 --> 00:06:58.420
Oh. no!

74
00:07:55.716 --> 00:07:56.988
I'm fine.

75
00:07:57.087 --> 00:07:58.398
Momo. I'm fine.

76
00:08:01.530 --> 00:08:04.480
We've got to get to Republic City.

77
00:08:04.481 --> 00:08:06.480
Appa. yip. yip!

78
00:08:23.104 --> 00:08:24.500
Water.

79
00:08:25.351 --> 00:08:28.401
Her tribes gather strength from the moon

80
00:08:29.085 --> 00:08:31.085
And flow with the tides.

81
00:08:32.229 --> 00:08:36.112
Earth. a kingdom of unshakable will.

82
00:08:36.562 --> 00:08:38.500
Reliable and strong.

83
00:08:42.378 --> 00:08:43.378
Fire.

84
00:08:44.618 --> 00:08:51.568
A nation capable of great
destruction. but also of great warmth.

85
00:08:53.985 --> 00:08:56.632
Air. peaceful nomads
with the power of a

86
00:08:56.633 --> 00:09:00.540
hurricane. but the
spirit of a gentle breeze.

87
00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:06.740
For generations. the
Avatar. the one master of

88
00:09:06.741 --> 00:09:11.540
all four elements. kept
the nations in balance.

89
00:09:12.791 --> 00:09:16.958
But when that responsibility
fell to me as a child. I ran away.

90
00:09:17.541 --> 00:09:19.933
I was caught in a deadly storm.

91
00:09:20.308 --> 00:09:27.574
but my Avatar spirit preserved me in a sphere
of energy where I stayed for 100 years.

92
00:09:27.616 --> 00:09:29.806
I woke to discover that
the balance preserved

93
00:09:29.831 --> 00:09:33.560
by the Avatar had
been destroyed by war.

94
00:09:34.856 --> 00:09:37.322
The air nomads were gone.

95
00:09:37.656 --> 00:09:38.656
All but one.

96
00:09:39.189 --> 00:09:40.189
Me.

97
00:09:41.056 --> 00:09:44.580
I could no longer run for my
responsibility as the Avatar.

98
00:09:45.835 --> 00:09:47.580
I found allies from every nation.

99
00:09:48.726 --> 00:09:51.580
Benders and non-benders.

100
00:09:52.926 --> 00:09:54.918
Katara taught me how to waterbend.

101
00:09:55.668 --> 00:09:58.468
Toph trained me in the
ways of the earthbenders.

102
00:09:59.235 --> 00:10:03.600
Zuko. once my worst enemy.
became my firebending teacher.

103
00:10:04.626 --> 00:10:09.035
Sokka showed me that bravery is the
most important part of being a leader.

104
00:10:10.301 --> 00:10:12.600
We became a family.

105
00:10:13.397 --> 00:10:16.600
And together. we ended
the Hundred Year War.

106
00:10:17.876 --> 00:10:22.620
Then. we began the hard
work of rebuilding the world.

107
00:10:34.089 --> 00:10:37.620
For so long. the nations
stood apart. alone.

108
00:10:37.969 --> 00:10:39.620
and we all suffered as a result.

109
00:10:40.369 --> 00:10:42.640
But here. on this ancient site.

110
00:10:43.331 --> 00:10:48.158
we created a place where all people are
welcome. bender and non-bender alike.

111
00:10:48.708 --> 00:10:52.074
working together in
peace to build the future.

112
00:10:52.674 --> 00:10:55.640
Though there are still those
who would seek to divide us.

113
00:10:56.039 --> 00:10:57.640
we remain united.

114
00:10:58.289 --> 00:10:59.916
As a council representative.

115
00:11:00.139 --> 00:11:05.033
I am honored to be here today celebrating
the anniversary of Republic City

116
00:11:05.549 --> 00:11:09.660
and the opening of Unity
Tower. a symbol for all people.

117
00:11:16.714 --> 00:11:18.660
Yes!

118
00:11:18.661 --> 00:11:20.660
It's the Avatar!

119
00:11:32.117 --> 00:11:33.449
Momo!

120
00:11:35.533 --> 00:11:36.895
[ Laughs ] Appa!

121
00:11:37.185 --> 00:11:39.531
I missed you. too. old friend.

122
00:11:41.584 --> 00:11:44.072
Aang!
Katara!

123
00:11:47.070 --> 00:11:49.800
You're hurt.

124
00:11:57.751 --> 00:11:58.751
Take a deep breath.

125
00:12:01.166 --> 00:12:03.700
[ Inhales deeply ] And exhale.

126
00:12:04.866 --> 00:12:07.131
I've heard the Denied
are growing in numbers.

127
00:12:07.183 --> 00:12:08.823
but they've never
done anything like this.

128
00:12:09.164 --> 00:12:10.720
Attacking the Avatar?

129
00:12:10.721 --> 00:12:11.721
Yeah.

130
00:12:12.269 --> 00:12:13.720
They were incredible fighters.

131
00:12:14.552 --> 00:12:15.603
even without bending.

132
00:12:15.721 --> 00:12:17.900
Oops!

133
00:12:17.925 --> 00:12:19.720
Ow!
Breathe through it.

134
00:12:20.619 --> 00:12:22.404
Be honest. You're enjoying this.

135
00:12:22.437 --> 00:12:24.744
Aang. this is serious.

136
00:12:24.769 --> 00:12:27.374
Whatever this map they
took was. if they were willing to

137
00:12:27.375 --> 00:12:31.049
kill the Avatar to get it. what
else are they willing to do?

138
00:12:31.755 --> 00:12:32.755
I don't know.

139
00:12:33.866 --> 00:12:35.533
I'm worried about you.

140
00:12:36.089 --> 00:12:40.043
You're spending more and
more time at the Air Temple. alone.

141
00:12:41.021 --> 00:12:44.360
It's how I hold on to my past.

142
00:12:45.555 --> 00:12:48.476
I know how hard this is for you.

143
00:12:52.159 --> 00:12:53.660
When I was attacked.

144
00:12:54.609 --> 00:12:59.760
all I could think about
was that... this could be it.

145
00:13:00.509 --> 00:13:03.760
I'm the last Airbender.

146
00:13:04.416 --> 00:13:05.542
If I die.

147
00:13:06.384 --> 00:13:08.480
my culture dies with me.

148
00:13:11.279 --> 00:13:12.780
You may be the last Airbender.

149
00:13:13.729 --> 00:13:15.587
but you're not alone.

150
00:13:16.228 --> 00:13:19.954
Aang. none of this would exist without you.

151
00:13:21.029 --> 00:13:25.780
You made the city possible
with your heart and your mind.

152
00:13:26.629 --> 00:13:30.800
Because of you. all of the
nations live here. together.

153
00:13:33.699 --> 00:13:35.470
All except mine.

154
00:13:45.212 --> 00:13:49.213
I know. but the people here
still need your protection.

155
00:13:50.147 --> 00:13:52.146
You're an Airbender.

156
00:13:52.879 --> 00:13:54.780
but you're also the Avatar.

157
00:13:56.929 --> 00:13:57.929
You're right.

158
00:13:59.579 --> 00:14:03.800
Whoever this Sonim person
is. I need to find out more.

159
00:14:29.265 --> 00:14:31.458
Aang.
Avatar Roku.

160
00:14:31.667 --> 00:14:33.796
It is good to see you again.

161
00:14:33.821 --> 00:14:35.633
How can I help you?

162
00:14:35.658 --> 00:14:39.779
In your lifetime. did you ever hear of
an ancient Airbender named Sonim?

163
00:14:40.169 --> 00:14:43.840
I have not. but you have
many past lives to call upon.

164
00:14:44.789 --> 00:14:48.840
Perhaps one further back in
the Avatar cycle can help you.

165
00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:50.840
Thank you. Avatar Roku.

166
00:14:53.408 --> 00:14:56.274
-I'm sorry. -I've never heard of Sonim.

167
00:14:56.474 --> 00:14:58.841
-Perhaps earlier. -You must go find him.
Not here. Not here.

168
00:15:08.976 --> 00:15:10.860
Um. hello?

169
00:15:11.708 --> 00:15:13.459
Is there anyone here?

170
00:15:14.395 --> 00:15:15.860
Hello?

171
00:15:16.112 --> 00:15:17.860
[ Grunts ]

172
00:15:17.861 --> 00:15:22.880
Who calls upon Avatar Xian's
vast wealth of knowledge.

173
00:15:24.881 --> 00:15:27.880
[ Coughing ] Oh. hello.

174
00:15:27.881 --> 00:15:31.880
You look like an Avatar from
a time quite distant from mine.

175
00:15:32.087 --> 00:15:35.004
Please. please. tell me about your era.

176
00:15:35.154 --> 00:15:36.880
What are people wearing?

177
00:15:36.881 --> 00:15:37.921
Are sandals still a thing?

178
00:15:38.279 --> 00:15:39.880
Uh. yes.

179
00:15:40.279 --> 00:15:41.880
Why? Why?

180
00:15:41.979 --> 00:15:48.900
After so many years. open toes. in
someone else's crusty cuticles. Disgusting.

181
00:15:48.901 --> 00:15:49.901
Right.

182
00:15:50.299 --> 00:15:51.900
Anyway. I have come through guidance.

183
00:15:51.901 --> 00:15:53.900
You see. I was attacked.

184
00:15:54.175 --> 00:15:55.876
It was not me. okay? It wasn't me.

185
00:15:55.901 --> 00:15:56.901
I know that.

186
00:15:57.589 --> 00:16:01.056
I think it might have something to
do with an Airbender named Sonim.

187
00:16:01.989 --> 00:16:04.254
Sonim. It sounds familiar.

188
00:16:04.799 --> 00:16:06.900
Sonim. Where have I heard that name before?

189
00:16:07.199 --> 00:16:09.830
Aha! Sonim was the youngest
daughter of the owner of

190
00:16:09.831 --> 00:16:11.920
the possum chicken shop
at the corner marketplace.

191
00:16:11.921 --> 00:16:14.920
Wait. That was my ex. Soniam.

192
00:16:14.921 --> 00:16:17.920
If only she didn't have
those humongous toenails.

193
00:16:17.921 --> 00:16:19.920
Ugh. Disgusting.

194
00:16:19.921 --> 00:16:21.920
This is going nowhere.
Soname?

195
00:16:23.919 --> 00:16:26.064
Well. thank you for your time.

196
00:16:26.089 --> 00:16:27.789
I must continue my search.

197
00:16:27.856 --> 00:16:29.831
Oh! Sonim!

198
00:16:29.856 --> 00:16:33.940
You're asking about the
legend of the lost Avatar.

199
00:16:34.570 --> 00:16:35.940
Sonim was an Avatar?

200
00:16:35.941 --> 00:16:37.737
Indeed she was.

201
00:16:38.120 --> 00:16:42.270
She was the Avatar in the
golden age of Airbender.

202
00:16:42.504 --> 00:16:47.129
Legend said she had a staff
that could channel the vast energy

203
00:16:47.154 --> 00:16:50.936
of the spirit world. granting
its keeper unlimited power.

204
00:16:51.662 --> 00:16:53.960
Is... Is that even possible?

205
00:16:55.343 --> 00:16:57.268
We'll never know for sure.

206
00:16:57.293 --> 00:16:59.642
Many Avatars have tried
to communicate with her.

207
00:16:59.667 --> 00:17:00.667
but they couldn't.

208
00:17:00.801 --> 00:17:05.233
She disappeared so completely
that it was as if she never existed.

209
00:17:05.975 --> 00:17:08.408
And perhaps it's better that way.

210
00:17:08.433 --> 00:17:11.980
Maybe such a staff was too
dangerous for anyone to possess.

211
00:17:12.879 --> 00:17:14.958
Even the Avatar.

212
00:17:15.324 --> 00:17:17.204
But... But that's exactly
why I need to find it.

213
00:17:17.529 --> 00:17:19.979
The people who attacked
me discovered a map.

214
00:17:19.980 --> 00:17:21.980
It must lead to the staff.

215
00:17:22.129 --> 00:17:24.374
Avatar Xian. please.

216
00:17:24.399 --> 00:17:25.980
You have to tell me where it is.

217
00:17:28.904 --> 00:17:35.000
The legend says that Sonim disappeared
with her staff on the peak of Mount Baihu.

218
00:17:37.299 --> 00:17:40.000
Katara. I'm sorry to leave so suddenly.

219
00:17:40.299 --> 00:17:43.000
but I found out what the Denied are after.

220
00:17:43.349 --> 00:17:45.980
Sonim had a staff of immense power.

221
00:17:46.129 --> 00:17:49.980
And in their hands. it could
be a devastating weapon.

222
00:17:49.981 --> 00:17:51.980
They have a head start.

223
00:17:51.981 --> 00:17:54.366
There's no time to waste.

224
00:17:54.483 --> 00:17:57.316
You take Appa and Momo and
gather up the rest of the team.

225
00:17:57.466 --> 00:17:58.980
We're gonna need some help.

226
00:18:05.592 --> 00:18:08.201
Next on the agenda. a
Fire Nation naval vessel

227
00:18:08.226 --> 00:18:12.000
came into conflict with an extremist
group of non-Benders called the Denied.

228
00:18:12.549 --> 00:18:15.001
They've been robbing
ancient sites... Your Majesty!

229
00:18:15.499 --> 00:18:18.000
An urgent message has
arrived from Republic City.

230
00:18:18.001 --> 00:18:19.001
How impudent.

231
00:18:19.449 --> 00:18:22.299
Can't you see Fire Lord
Zuko is... Chamberlain.

232
00:18:23.269 --> 00:18:25.174
There's only one person
who can send a message

233
00:18:25.199 --> 00:18:27.199
urgent enough to interrupt
the Fire Lord's counsel.

234
00:18:27.819 --> 00:18:29.020
Is it from the Avatar?

235
00:18:29.021 --> 00:18:31.524
Yes. my lord. Read
it to me. Yes. my lord.

236
00:18:35.345 --> 00:18:37.021
Um...
What are you doing?

237
00:18:37.120 --> 00:18:38.120
Read it quickly.

238
00:18:38.619 --> 00:18:40.020
Uh. y-y-yes. Grand Chamberlain.

239
00:18:40.194 --> 00:18:42.020
[ Clears throat ]

240
00:18:42.369 --> 00:18:45.040
Flameo Hartman. house
ruling the Fire Nation.

241
00:18:45.041 --> 00:18:48.041
I hope the boring Chamberlain
you mentioned... [ Clears throat ]

242
00:18:48.089 --> 00:18:51.040
in your letters isn't
still annoying you.

243
00:18:51.041 --> 00:18:54.040
Anywho. to cut to the
chase. I need your help.

244
00:18:54.041 --> 00:18:56.040
Can you please come immediately?

245
00:18:56.314 --> 00:19:00.040
Oh. and don't forget to
bring some firecracker buns.

246
00:19:00.041 --> 00:19:02.040
[ Sighs ]

247
00:19:03.608 --> 00:19:06.316
Allow me to present Sokka Cycle.

248
00:19:06.341 --> 00:19:10.060
Flames launch you into the sky where
you can drop water bombs on your enemies.

249
00:19:10.061 --> 00:19:13.060
Then skis pop out to
help you stick the landing.

250
00:19:13.856 --> 00:19:15.060
Pretty great. right?

251
00:19:15.061 --> 00:19:16.061
Eh. boring.

252
00:19:16.159 --> 00:19:18.060
Why would you need a sled
when you can just waterbend?

253
00:19:18.061 --> 00:19:19.060
Oh. oh. oh. like me. like me!

254
00:19:19.061 --> 00:19:21.060
Whee!

255
00:19:21.309 --> 00:19:24.080
Keep in mind. there's still plenty
of folks like me who can't bend.

256
00:19:24.081 --> 00:19:27.080
Why would Avatar Aang
partner with a non-bender?

257
00:19:27.081 --> 00:19:29.080
Ugh. Why?
I'll tell you why.

258
00:19:29.081 --> 00:19:31.080
I saved him from the iceberg.

259
00:19:31.081 --> 00:19:35.080
My boomerang flew by his side while I
carried away enemies with my trusty blade.

260
00:19:35.081 --> 00:19:38.699
I even took down the whole
Fire Nation airship armada.

261
00:19:40.783 --> 00:19:44.100
And on top of all that. I
was more popular than him.

262
00:19:45.149 --> 00:19:46.100
You're such a liar. Sokka.

263
00:19:49.101 --> 00:19:51.100
It's from the Avatar.
Wow!

264
00:19:51.101 --> 00:19:52.101
Really?

265
00:19:52.374 --> 00:19:54.100
Oh. so now you think I'm cool?

266
00:19:56.101 --> 00:19:57.922
All right. metalbenders.

267
00:19:58.156 --> 00:19:59.400
Let's see if any of you tenderfoots

268
00:19:59.424 --> 00:20:01.120
can at least make me use my hands.

269
00:20:35.141 --> 00:20:39.140
I'm still the greatest
earthbender in the world!

270
00:20:39.141 --> 00:20:40.491
And I'm bored.

271
00:20:41.324 --> 00:20:43.140
M-Master Toph. there's a bird on your head.

272
00:20:43.141 --> 00:20:44.141
And?

273
00:20:44.589 --> 00:20:46.140
It looks like it has a message.

274
00:20:46.239 --> 00:20:47.239
Read.

275
00:20:48.209 --> 00:20:50.210
Uh. it's from Avatar Aang.
He needs your help.

276
00:20:50.260 --> 00:20:53.160
It's the Denied?
Where is he?

277
00:20:53.309 --> 00:20:55.160
Mount Bihu.

278
00:21:56.737 --> 00:21:58.160
No. no. no!

279
00:21:58.820 --> 00:22:00.160
No.

280
00:22:03.161 --> 00:22:05.160
I love that hat.

281
00:23:49.749 --> 00:23:51.080
Sonam?

282
00:23:56.101 --> 00:23:58.100
Could that be you?

283
00:25:00.739 --> 00:25:02.160
Who are you?

284
00:29:06.449 --> 00:29:08.994
How did he hold up an entire mountain?

285
00:29:09.028 --> 00:29:13.400
His chi is strong. like
nothing I've ever felt.

286
00:29:13.599 --> 00:29:18.400
Hey. Avatar. you think this guy beat
your record for longest frozen airbender?

287
00:29:18.449 --> 00:29:21.400
Yeah.
How long do you think he was in that ice?

288
00:29:21.599 --> 00:29:25.420
I don't know. His tattoos look ancient.

289
00:29:26.069 --> 00:29:27.976
He's been in there a long time.

290
00:29:28.009 --> 00:29:29.420
He smells good for an old guy.

291
00:29:29.421 --> 00:29:30.421
Ew.

292
00:29:30.446 --> 00:29:32.420
What? My senses tell me
this guy is pretty attractive.

293
00:29:32.421 --> 00:29:35.420
-Toph!
-Someone else confirmed. 
This is serious. What does "attractive" even mean?

294
00:29:35.421 --> 00:29:37.420
Just give me a straight confirmation.

295
00:29:37.421 --> 00:29:39.421
Is he attractive?
He's very attractive.

296
00:29:39.446 --> 00:29:40.651
Huh?

297
00:29:41.519 --> 00:29:44.440
What? He is.
It's all in the bone structure.

298
00:29:44.951 --> 00:29:46.440
No.

299
00:29:46.441 --> 00:29:49.440
No.
No!

300
00:29:49.441 --> 00:29:51.440
Whoa. whoa. whoa. Hey.

301
00:29:51.441 --> 00:29:53.440
Easy. You're safe.

302
00:29:56.749 --> 00:29:59.440
Earthbender!
No. no. no. We're all friends here.

303
00:29:59.441 --> 00:30:00.441
It's okay.

304
00:30:00.589 --> 00:30:03.460
Someone woke up on the
wrong side of the mountain.

305
00:30:03.959 --> 00:30:06.460
Where is she?

306
00:30:06.659 --> 00:30:08.460
Where is Avatar Sonim?

307
00:30:08.759 --> 00:30:10.460
You knew Sonim?

308
00:30:11.359 --> 00:30:12.460
Who are you?

309
00:30:13.659 --> 00:30:18.460
I don't know how to explain it. but
you've been asleep for a long time.

310
00:30:19.084 --> 00:30:20.460
I'm the Avatar now.

311
00:30:21.009 --> 00:30:22.460
I'm Aang.

312
00:30:23.109 --> 00:30:28.792
If you're the Avatar. then Sonim.

313
00:30:30.779 --> 00:30:33.647
Well. Sonim might be
long gone. but on the

314
00:30:33.648 --> 00:30:37.080
bright side. you woke
up at the perfect time.

315
00:30:37.105 --> 00:30:39.754
Everyone will be amazed
to see another Airbender.

316
00:30:39.779 --> 00:30:42.480
Aang's not the last one anymore.

317
00:30:43.379 --> 00:30:45.500
What do you mean. "last"?

318
00:30:45.501 --> 00:30:47.059
Oh.

319
00:30:49.999 --> 00:30:51.500
The Air Nomads.

320
00:30:52.199 --> 00:30:54.500
They've been wiped out.

321
00:30:55.199 --> 00:30:57.500
There's only me.

322
00:30:58.274 --> 00:30:59.500
No.

323
00:31:00.249 --> 00:31:02.500
Sonim Staff. do you have it?

324
00:31:03.486 --> 00:31:05.611
It's our only hope now.

325
00:31:05.636 --> 00:31:07.094
What do you mean?

326
00:31:07.119 --> 00:31:08.520
I thought it was a weapon.

327
00:31:09.768 --> 00:31:11.369
The staff is no weapon.

328
00:31:12.319 --> 00:31:14.520
It is a gift.

329
00:31:15.984 --> 00:31:20.965
With it. Sonim was able to channel
the vast power of the spirit world.

330
00:31:21.619 --> 00:31:24.520
It was this power that
allowed Jurana to flourish.

331
00:31:24.769 --> 00:31:29.540
The greatest city in the
world. an Air Nomad utopia.

332
00:31:30.114 --> 00:31:33.540
where Sonim presided
over a golden age of balance.

333
00:31:33.541 --> 00:31:37.540
and where I devoted
my life to serving her.

334
00:31:37.839 --> 00:31:41.378
In return. she raised me
up and used her staff to give

335
00:31:41.403 --> 00:31:46.560
me. a lowly non-Bender.
the power to bend the air.

336
00:31:47.659 --> 00:31:50.559
I was the first. but I
would not be the last.

337
00:31:50.560 --> 00:31:54.488
She filled the skies with
Airbenders. and we flew

338
00:31:54.489 --> 00:31:58.560
by her side. spreading
peace across the world.

339
00:32:07.009 --> 00:32:09.580
Aang. are you okay?

340
00:32:10.728 --> 00:32:13.580
Sonim used the staff to
give people Airbending.

341
00:32:14.329 --> 00:32:16.380
If we found it.

342
00:32:17.529 --> 00:32:20.051
I could bring Airbending back to the world.

343
00:32:20.579 --> 00:32:21.580
This is incredible.

344
00:32:21.581 --> 00:32:24.579
There haven't been Airbenders
for over a hundred years.

345
00:32:24.580 --> 00:32:28.600
This is everything you ever wanted. Aang.

346
00:32:29.849 --> 00:32:33.600
We could heal the greatest atrocity
my nation committed in the war.

347
00:32:34.799 --> 00:32:37.600
This could be the final
step to rebuilding the world.

348
00:32:37.999 --> 00:32:39.600
Not if the Denied get there first.

349
00:32:39.999 --> 00:32:41.600
They have the map.

350
00:32:42.299 --> 00:32:43.600
Who are the Denied?

351
00:32:43.649 --> 00:32:45.600
A group of violent non-Benders.

352
00:32:45.999 --> 00:32:47.620
They... they must be after the staff

353
00:32:48.069 --> 00:32:50.259
to give themselves Airbending.

354
00:32:50.469 --> 00:32:51.669
Then there's no time to waste.

355
00:32:52.219 --> 00:32:53.620
There's only one place it could be.

356
00:32:53.621 --> 00:32:57.620
Ready your bison. We'll need to
travel across the endless ocean.

357
00:32:58.244 --> 00:32:59.620
On the other side of the world?

358
00:33:00.119 --> 00:33:01.620
But there's nothing out there.

359
00:33:01.621 --> 00:33:04.620
There's an island.
The journey will not be easy.

360
00:33:04.969 --> 00:33:06.640
but we can make it.

361
00:33:07.489 --> 00:33:08.640
Then let's get going.

362
00:33:09.189 --> 00:33:12.640
The skies are no place for a water child.

363
00:33:12.739 --> 00:33:14.640
Water child?

364
00:33:14.889 --> 00:33:17.979
Um. I know you just
woke up after thousands

365
00:33:17.980 --> 00:33:20.640
of years. but we do
these things together.

366
00:33:20.641 --> 00:33:22.640
Trust me. we're stronger this way.

367
00:33:23.039 --> 00:33:24.640
Welcome to Team Avatar.

368
00:33:25.289 --> 00:33:26.640
What's your name?

369
00:33:27.189 --> 00:33:29.660
Tagah. My name is Tagah.

370
00:33:39.641 --> 00:33:42.640
Just think of it as a big metal air bison.

371
00:33:50.641 --> 00:33:54.640
We will travel ancient
paths through the sky.

372
00:33:54.939 --> 00:33:57.780
ones that our people
learned by following the great

373
00:33:57.781 --> 00:34:00.660
air bison herds that long
ago taught us Airbending.

374
00:34:00.661 --> 00:34:07.660
Air currents known only to us.
encircling the great sphere of existence.

375
00:34:07.661 --> 00:34:14.659
allowing us to travel where we wish.
giving us our name. the Air Nomads.

376
00:34:44.830 --> 00:34:46.679
What's he doing?

377
00:34:46.930 --> 00:34:48.679
He's really feeling that air.

378
00:34:49.780 --> 00:34:51.699
He's navigating by instinct.

379
00:34:51.875 --> 00:34:53.699
What if his instincts are just wrong?

380
00:34:53.700 --> 00:34:56.699
Who needs instincts when
you've got muscles like that?

381
00:34:56.750 --> 00:34:58.700
Or what if his brain is
messed up from being frozen?

382
00:34:58.701 --> 00:34:59.701
Like me?

383
00:34:59.800 --> 00:35:02.288
Uh. no. no!

384
00:35:02.313 --> 00:35:04.700
He was frozen for 5.000 years. okay?

385
00:35:04.800 --> 00:35:06.700
You were frozen for. what. 100?

386
00:35:06.701 --> 00:35:07.850
Okay. that's nothing.

387
00:35:07.875 --> 00:35:11.221
Your brain is... fresh.

388
00:35:11.905 --> 00:35:14.720
Maybe he is a little
old-fashioned. but look at him.

389
00:35:15.170 --> 00:35:17.163
He's so in tune with his
element. he can travel

390
00:35:17.164 --> 00:35:21.720
across the entire ocean
with no map. no instruments.

391
00:35:24.721 --> 00:35:26.720
There's so much I can learn from him.

392
00:35:38.741 --> 00:35:42.740
I'd give anything to be able
to see my air bison again.

393
00:35:45.434 --> 00:35:49.534
And now. to see only one remains.

394
00:35:51.247 --> 00:35:52.580
Aang

395
00:35:53.240 --> 00:35:56.760
You said our people were
wiped out. yet you survived.

396
00:35:57.610 --> 00:35:58.760
How?

397
00:36:00.660 --> 00:36:02.760
I had just found out I was the Avatar.

398
00:36:04.471 --> 00:36:07.760
but the responsibility... it was too much.

399
00:36:09.201 --> 00:36:10.760
So I ran away.

400
00:36:12.060 --> 00:36:15.780
And while I was gone.
the Fire Nation attacked.

401
00:36:17.684 --> 00:36:19.384
They were looking for me.

402
00:36:21.584 --> 00:36:24.780
If... If I'd just been there...

403
00:36:25.180 --> 00:36:26.680
Sonam would say.

404
00:36:26.980 --> 00:36:29.780
"Air nomads are formed from the mist.

405
00:36:30.280 --> 00:36:32.780
We walk the world for a moment in time.

406
00:36:33.180 --> 00:36:36.800
Then we return
to the eternal wind.

407
00:36:38.000 --> 00:36:39.800
Monk Gyatso taught me that.

408
00:36:40.700 --> 00:36:41.800
We carry the same weight.

409
00:36:42.700 --> 00:36:45.800
a grief no one else could
possibly comprehend.

410
00:36:46.000 --> 00:36:48.742
But you and I can heal the past.

411
00:36:49.176 --> 00:36:54.800
Let me show you how powerful our element
can be when airbenders work together.

412
00:36:57.376 --> 00:36:58.480
Aah!

413
00:36:58.481 --> 00:37:00.820
What are you doing?!
Aah!

414
00:37:00.821 --> 00:37:02.820
This is how Sonam taught me!

415
00:37:02.821 --> 00:37:05.820
Feel the energy that tethers us.

416
00:37:10.821 --> 00:37:14.820
The bond between us... can you feel it?
Use it!

417
00:37:14.821 --> 00:37:16.840
This is amazing!

418
00:37:21.328 --> 00:37:22.563
[ Laughs ] Whoo-hoo!

419
00:37:22.564 --> 00:37:24.542
Oh. yeah!

420
00:37:24.792 --> 00:37:25.984
Human boomerang!

421
00:37:26.009 --> 00:37:27.201
He's actually flying.

422
00:37:27.226 --> 00:37:28.659
So are we.

423
00:37:29.009 --> 00:37:31.142
Whoa! That's my best friend!
That's my best friend!

424
00:37:32.159 --> 00:37:33.840
No. you throw me!

425
00:38:01.881 --> 00:38:03.880
I had no idea this was possible!

426
00:38:04.782 --> 00:38:06.949
This is only the beginning.

427
00:38:13.996 --> 00:38:15.616
I can't believe it.

428
00:38:16.250 --> 00:38:17.900
Airbenders will fill the sky again.

429
00:38:18.600 --> 00:38:20.900
We have been given a great gift...

430
00:38:21.400 --> 00:38:22.900
the chance to redeem ourselves.

431
00:38:23.850 --> 00:38:26.607
You were destined to find
me on that mountain. Aang.

432
00:38:28.700 --> 00:38:30.900
How did you end up there?

433
00:38:34.400 --> 00:38:36.900
The earthbenders had attacked Jurana.

434
00:38:37.200 --> 00:38:39.920
Sonam and I fought
fearlessly. side by side.

435
00:38:40.570 --> 00:38:41.920
We drove them back to Mount Bahu.

436
00:38:42.870 --> 00:38:44.759
and that's the last I remember.

437
00:38:46.503 --> 00:38:48.059
She must have saved your life.

438
00:38:48.870 --> 00:38:51.920
Only an Avatar could
have put you in that sphere.

439
00:38:55.070 --> 00:38:57.940
Aang. can I ask you something?

440
00:38:57.941 --> 00:38:58.941
Of course.

441
00:38:59.790 --> 00:39:02.940
If the Fire Nation
destroyed the Air Nomads.

442
00:39:03.389 --> 00:39:06.589
how can you suffer the
presence of the Fire Lord?

443
00:39:09.290 --> 00:39:10.940
Zuko is a friend and an ally.

444
00:39:11.840 --> 00:39:14.940
He turned against his own
father to help me end the war.

445
00:39:15.340 --> 00:39:17.960
Yet he wears the crown himself now.

446
00:39:18.610 --> 00:39:21.960
Fire. by its nature. burns. Aang.

447
00:39:22.310 --> 00:39:23.960
Our kind have always suffered

448
00:39:24.060 --> 00:39:26.960
at the hands of the other elements.

449
00:39:27.260 --> 00:39:28.960
That's why we built Republic City...

450
00:39:29.760 --> 00:39:31.960
to show the world that
if we listen to each other.

451
00:39:32.360 --> 00:39:35.960
we can all live together in peace.

452
00:39:36.235 --> 00:39:40.592
And once we bring back
airbenders. it'll be complete.

453
00:39:43.780 --> 00:39:45.100
When everyone stuck to their own.

454
00:39:45.930 --> 00:39:47.980
the whole world was nearly torn apart.

455
00:39:49.080 --> 00:39:52.980
And besides. Katara. Sokka. Zuko. Toph.

456
00:39:53.530 --> 00:39:54.980
they're my family now.

457
00:39:56.480 --> 00:39:59.000
I want to live in a world
where we can all be together.

458
00:40:00.900 --> 00:40:03.363
You remind me so much of Sonam.

459
00:40:08.163 --> 00:40:09.905
It's the Avatar.

460
00:40:09.930 --> 00:40:11.946
And this time. he's got
his friends with them.

461
00:40:12.163 --> 00:40:13.655
That's the Fire Lord's airship.

462
00:40:13.680 --> 00:40:14.955
How'd they get ahead of us?

463
00:40:14.980 --> 00:40:16.140
They don't even have the map.

464
00:40:16.300 --> 00:40:18.778
We can't risk him
getting to the staff first.

465
00:40:18.919 --> 00:40:19.953
Kill him.

466
00:40:19.978 --> 00:40:21.020
But he spared our lives.

467
00:40:21.045 --> 00:40:25.020
And how many Countless were killed in
the hundred years waiting for his return?

468
00:40:25.120 --> 00:40:28.020
Where was he when
your family was wiped out?

469
00:40:28.021 --> 00:40:33.020
If we want anything to change. we
need what the benders have... power.

470
00:40:40.786 --> 00:40:42.274
Fire!

471
00:40:48.058 --> 00:40:49.590
It's the Denied.

472
00:40:51.213 --> 00:40:54.384
Uh. we are definitely under attack.

473
00:40:56.236 --> 00:40:57.884
Tear them to shreads!

474
00:41:09.702 --> 00:41:12.702
Is he crushing the ship?

475
00:41:12.727 --> 00:41:15.526
Tagah?

476
00:41:15.753 --> 00:41:17.752
Tagah. stop!

477
00:41:42.535 --> 00:41:43.969
We're here.

478
00:41:45.711 --> 00:41:47.745
The Immortal Storm.

479
00:41:48.003 --> 00:41:49.369
Oh. no.

480
00:41:54.603 --> 00:41:56.884
There has to be another way around.

481
00:41:56.967 --> 00:41:59.224
No. Together. you and I
can clear a path for the ship.

482
00:41:59.249 --> 00:42:01.230
But we have to go now.

483
00:42:01.996 --> 00:42:03.736
Aang. trust me.

484
00:42:07.046 --> 00:42:09.630
Uh. maybe now's a good time to turn back.

485
00:42:09.913 --> 00:42:12.179
I don't think that's an option anymore.

486
00:42:12.204 --> 00:42:14.203
Where are they going?

487
00:42:21.686 --> 00:42:24.649
The engine's out.
We're losing air pressure.

488
00:42:30.199 --> 00:42:31.317
Katara. come with me.

489
00:42:31.342 --> 00:42:33.020
What about me?
Take the wheel.

490
00:42:33.021 --> 00:42:36.020
What? I've only ever
crashed Fire Nation airships.

491
00:42:38.184 --> 00:42:41.020
Okay. let's see. Here's our rudder.
This is the elevator. There's our ballast.

492
00:42:41.021 --> 00:42:44.020
And there's the giant tornado
that's going to kill us all.

493
00:42:47.327 --> 00:42:49.011
Follow my lead.

494
00:42:59.628 --> 00:43:01.020
Work with me.

495
00:43:01.021 --> 00:43:02.021
Just like I showed you.

496
00:43:03.020 --> 00:43:04.020
We can harness it.

497
00:43:14.555 --> 00:43:17.020
Yes! That's it. Aang. Keep going.

498
00:43:29.865 --> 00:43:31.117
Got it.

499
00:43:34.020 --> 00:43:36.020
Zuko! Zuko!

500
00:43:36.021 --> 00:43:39.020
Aang and Tagah are destroying
tornadoes. but there's too many!

501
00:43:39.021 --> 00:43:41.020
And they're everywhere!

502
00:43:41.021 --> 00:43:43.020
Just steer the ship. Don't lose Aang.

503
00:43:43.021 --> 00:43:46.146
It's not that easy. especially
when everything is sideways.

504
00:43:46.287 --> 00:43:48.286
Okay. left!

505
00:43:56.882 --> 00:43:58.680
I did it!

506
00:43:59.303 --> 00:44:00.862
Right!

507
00:44:08.871 --> 00:44:11.871
Oh no. we're falling behind!

508
00:44:11.896 --> 00:44:14.671
I'm losing sight of them.
We have to go back.

509
00:44:14.719 --> 00:44:18.718
Trust in your friends. They won't
make it if we don't clear a path.

510
00:44:31.021 --> 00:44:34.020
Zuko. we're going to crash into the sea!

511
00:44:34.021 --> 00:44:37.020
When I give you the signal.
pull the lever next to the wheel.

512
00:44:41.782 --> 00:44:43.629
We're going to crash! We're going to crash!

513
00:44:43.654 --> 00:44:45.653
Katara?

514
00:45:04.718 --> 00:45:06.455
Give me the signal! Give me the signal!

515
00:45:10.688 --> 00:45:11.688
Whoa!

516
00:45:13.738 --> 00:45:15.462
Sokka. now!

517
00:45:15.487 --> 00:45:17.486
Here we go!

518
00:45:39.107 --> 00:45:41.107
Katara! We did it!

519
00:45:42.297 --> 00:45:43.980
What were you thinking?

520
00:45:44.005 --> 00:45:46.004
I was clearing the
tornadoes to make a path.

521
00:45:46.029 --> 00:45:48.232
The ship almost crashed. Aang.
We could have died.

522
00:45:48.257 --> 00:45:51.256
And what if you got yourself killed?
You're the Avatar.

523
00:45:51.281 --> 00:45:54.280
This is too risky.
We need to turn back now.

524
00:45:54.305 --> 00:45:57.304
No! We're almost there.

525
00:45:57.329 --> 00:45:59.328
We just need to get
to the eye of the storm.

526
00:45:59.353 --> 00:46:01.352
Aang. no!

527
00:46:01.377 --> 00:46:03.126
Aang. no! This is too dangerous.

528
00:46:03.151 --> 00:46:06.150
The staff is out there.
They denied her after it.

529
00:46:06.175 --> 00:46:07.993
Do you really believe that they
could make it through the storm?

530
00:46:08.017 --> 00:46:11.016
We're nearly there.
That staff can bring back my people.

531
00:46:11.041 --> 00:46:15.040
I understand how much you want that. but...
You don't understand. None of you do.

532
00:46:16.220 --> 00:46:21.594
Aang... We push forward.

533
00:46:24.253 --> 00:46:29.107
If we generate enough air.
we can push our way through.

534
00:47:12.887 --> 00:47:14.020
We're alive?

535
00:47:14.470 --> 00:47:17.020
We made it through. Thank you. Tagah.

536
00:47:17.120 --> 00:47:20.020
It was you. Aang.
We're here because of you.

537
00:47:20.021 --> 00:47:22.020
Yeah. we're having a good time. too.

538
00:47:22.045 --> 00:47:24.020
You could have told us we were
flying into the Immortal Storm.

539
00:47:24.021 --> 00:47:27.020
I know it was dangerous.
but we had to risk it.

540
00:47:27.070 --> 00:47:30.020
We? I don't remember
when we took a vote on that.

541
00:47:30.470 --> 00:47:32.020
There wasn't time. I had to make a call.

542
00:47:32.021 --> 00:47:34.020
Friends. please. don't blame Aang.

543
00:47:34.920 --> 00:47:38.020
This is all my fault.
I knew this would be difficult.

544
00:47:38.920 --> 00:47:41.020
But Aang believed in
your strength as a team.

545
00:47:41.720 --> 00:47:43.120
And I'm honored to be a part of it.

546
00:47:49.451 --> 00:47:51.020
I forgive you. Tagah.

547
00:47:51.670 --> 00:47:53.020
Everyone. look.

548
00:47:54.770 --> 00:47:58.020
These islands... they were... lion turtles.

549
00:48:00.661 --> 00:48:01.772
Whoa!

550
00:48:01.905 --> 00:48:04.020
It's beautiful.

551
00:48:07.061 --> 00:48:12.988
Long before my time. the lion turtles
granted the gift of bending to humans.

552
00:48:13.120 --> 00:48:15.020
These are their final resting grounds.

553
00:48:16.220 --> 00:48:19.020
This is where Sonim
came to learn their ways.

554
00:48:20.320 --> 00:48:23.020
I am certain that she left her staff here.

555
00:48:23.720 --> 00:48:25.020
Where should we start looking?

556
00:48:25.370 --> 00:48:28.020
Aang. you must connect with her.

557
00:48:29.195 --> 00:48:32.020
But no one can connect with Sonim.

558
00:48:32.220 --> 00:48:35.020
The spiritual power of the lion
turtles is still concentrated here.

559
00:48:36.070 --> 00:48:39.020
Let it guide you.
We'll set out immediately.

560
00:48:39.270 --> 00:48:42.020
Actually. Tagah. we could
really use your help here.

561
00:48:42.070 --> 00:48:45.020
If the denied are close
behind. we need to be ready.

562
00:48:45.195 --> 00:48:49.020
Yeah. and we're gonna need more
than Toph's metal bending to fix this.

563
00:48:49.470 --> 00:48:52.020
My bending got us through that storm.
What did you do?

564
00:48:52.021 --> 00:48:53.021
Steered with his feet.

565
00:48:53.320 --> 00:48:56.569
Repairs can wait. Aang needs me.

566
00:48:56.770 --> 00:49:00.020
Tagah. please. stay and help my friends.

567
00:49:01.170 --> 00:49:02.853
I'll be okay on my own.

568
00:49:03.196 --> 00:49:05.195
As you wish.

569
00:49:05.220 --> 00:49:08.013
We will begin repairs for our voyage home.

570
00:49:09.635 --> 00:49:13.020
Everyone. I know I've asked
a lot of you on this journey.

571
00:49:13.021 --> 00:49:17.020
But we're about to accomplish
something that will change the world.

572
00:50:09.021 --> 00:50:10.021
Let it guide you.

573
00:50:27.289 --> 00:50:29.453
Sonam?

574
00:50:46.670 --> 00:50:50.532
Oh. this is turning out
to be a nice little vacation.

575
00:50:50.576 --> 00:50:54.107
Aside from all the people trying
to kill us. and the tornadoes.

576
00:50:54.132 --> 00:50:56.797
Um. we're supposed to be fixing the ship?

577
00:50:56.822 --> 00:50:58.776
You're doing great. buddy.

578
00:50:59.270 --> 00:51:00.810
Has anyone seen Tagah?

579
00:51:00.835 --> 00:51:03.020
Yes. we've all seen
Tagah. He's so gorgeous.

580
00:51:03.021 --> 00:51:05.677
Geez. I get it.

581
00:51:05.702 --> 00:51:07.020
Oh. I see what you mean.

582
00:51:07.021 --> 00:51:08.506
He wandered off that way.

583
00:51:08.531 --> 00:51:10.530
No. maybe that way?

584
00:51:44.580 --> 00:51:46.474
Tagah

585
00:51:46.558 --> 00:51:48.108
Where are you going?

586
00:51:48.540 --> 00:51:50.528
Aang needs to be protected.

587
00:51:50.553 --> 00:51:52.025
I agree.

588
00:51:54.363 --> 00:51:57.020
I know my ways may seem unusual to you.

589
00:51:57.270 --> 00:52:01.558
But I assure you. everything
I do. I do for Aang.

590
00:52:01.980 --> 00:52:04.020
For Aang? Or for the staff?

591
00:52:05.892 --> 00:52:08.020
You have no idea all that we've lost.

592
00:52:08.720 --> 00:52:11.020
You've never known a world with airbenders.

593
00:52:11.445 --> 00:52:13.020
I know Aang.

594
00:52:13.770 --> 00:52:16.047
He may be the last of his kind.

595
00:52:16.072 --> 00:52:18.020
But he's the reason this world knows peace.

596
00:52:22.501 --> 00:52:26.020
His values as an air nomad
have brought balance to chaos.

597
00:52:29.029 --> 00:52:31.915
It's because of Aang
that the Water Tribes.

598
00:52:31.940 --> 00:52:35.020
Earth Kingdom. and Fire
Nation now work together.

599
00:52:35.021 --> 00:52:37.666
Striving for harmony.

600
00:52:37.691 --> 00:52:41.002
A peace we once thought unattainable.

601
00:52:42.624 --> 00:52:44.513
You speak of peace.

602
00:52:44.538 --> 00:52:47.020
There will never be
peace among the elements.

603
00:52:47.021 --> 00:52:52.020
There never was. Your precious
Republic City is built on lies.

604
00:52:52.021 --> 00:52:54.286
It's built on hope.

605
00:52:54.311 --> 00:52:56.020
Do you have hope. Tagah?

606
00:52:56.021 --> 00:52:59.020
Saving my people requires
more than just hope.

607
00:52:59.095 --> 00:53:01.020
It requires sacrifice.

608
00:53:01.070 --> 00:53:04.020
I saw you try to crush
the denied's airships.

609
00:53:04.095 --> 00:53:06.020
You were ready to kill them.

610
00:53:08.146 --> 00:53:10.949
I know what kind of airbender Aang is.

611
00:53:12.969 --> 00:53:16.020
But what kind of airbender are you?

612
00:53:44.021 --> 00:53:46.020
Aang did well getting us here.

613
00:53:46.021 --> 00:53:50.020
There is great strength in
him. but weakness as well.

614
00:53:50.045 --> 00:53:51.710
Weakness?

615
00:53:51.735 --> 00:53:54.020
Yes. you.

616
00:54:10.021 --> 00:54:12.020
What the hog monkey?

617
00:54:34.921 --> 00:54:37.025
He trusted you.

618
00:54:43.669 --> 00:54:44.669
No.

619
00:56:04.961 --> 00:56:06.918
Brother.

620
00:56:09.270 --> 00:56:12.340
Tagah. it's real.

621
00:56:15.687 --> 00:56:19.223
We can finally bring back airbending.

622
00:56:21.356 --> 00:56:22.996
Let's go tell the others.

623
00:56:23.021 --> 00:56:27.020
We can do this. me and you.

624
00:56:27.021 --> 00:56:31.020
I can't do this without my friends.

625
00:56:31.021 --> 00:56:34.020
Earth killed my people. fire killed yours.

626
00:56:34.520 --> 00:56:38.020
The staff is the only way we
can create a new air empire.

627
00:56:38.420 --> 00:56:41.020
One capable of defending itself.

628
00:56:41.021 --> 00:56:44.020
No. we can build a new future. Tagah.

629
00:56:44.220 --> 00:56:46.020
But it has to be for everyone.

630
00:56:46.095 --> 00:56:48.020
The staff doesn't belong to everyone.

631
00:56:48.320 --> 00:56:50.020
It belongs to us.

632
00:56:50.021 --> 00:56:52.020
What have you done?

633
00:56:52.021 --> 00:56:55.020
As long as they were around. you
always put them ahead of our people.

634
00:56:55.845 --> 00:56:57.020
Don't you see?

635
00:56:57.021 --> 00:56:59.778
This is how we redeem ourselves.

636
00:56:59.803 --> 00:57:04.020
It doesn't matter that you ran then.
As long as you stand with me now.

637
00:57:04.021 --> 00:57:07.020
Aang. listen to me.
Katara.

638
00:57:07.021 --> 00:57:09.020
It's the only way.

639
00:57:22.021 --> 00:57:24.020
You're a traitor to your own.

640
00:57:24.021 --> 00:57:26.020
Just like Sonam.

641
00:58:04.021 --> 00:58:07.417
I wanted to do this with you by my side.

642
00:58:07.442 --> 00:58:12.065
But if I must build a new
air empire alone. so be it.

643
00:58:21.021 --> 00:58:24.020
There's no way in.
We have to turn back.

644
00:58:24.045 --> 00:58:27.809
No. we keep trying to push through.

645
00:58:39.021 --> 00:58:41.625
Sonam's staff.

646
00:58:41.669 --> 00:58:43.020
Denied.

647
00:58:43.021 --> 00:58:45.020
The Avatar is dead.

648
00:58:45.021 --> 00:58:50.020
If you wish to build a new world where
you have the power. I can give it to you.

649
00:59:04.844 --> 00:59:06.021
Appa.

650
00:59:06.770 --> 00:59:08.020
Katara.

651
00:59:08.170 --> 00:59:11.020
Katara.

652
00:59:11.021 --> 00:59:13.020
Katara.

653
00:59:13.270 --> 00:59:15.020
They're gone.

654
00:59:15.120 --> 00:59:17.020
It's all my fault.

655
00:59:17.270 --> 00:59:19.020
It's always been my fault.

656
00:59:19.670 --> 00:59:23.020
Ever since I ran away.

657
00:59:23.370 --> 00:59:28.782
No Avatar has ever fallen into such
shame as to join me here in my sorrow.

658
00:59:31.042 --> 00:59:33.160
Why do you grieve so. friend?

659
00:59:33.720 --> 00:59:38.020
Avatar Sonam?

660
00:59:38.320 --> 00:59:40.020
Tagah murdered my friends.

661
00:59:40.570 --> 00:59:42.020
And now he has the staff.

662
00:59:42.021 --> 00:59:44.020
Tagah.
No.

663
00:59:44.021 --> 00:59:45.021
No I

664
00:59:45.320 --> 00:59:47.020
I stopped him.

665
00:59:47.170 --> 00:59:49.020
I hit the staff.

666
00:59:49.170 --> 00:59:52.020
What have you done?

667
00:59:52.021 --> 00:59:54.020
You're the one who gave him airbending.

668
00:59:54.570 --> 00:59:57.020
How could you give power to a monster?

669
00:59:57.570 --> 01:00:02.020
The Tagah I gave bending
to was a different man.

670
01:00:02.855 --> 01:00:05.020
It was a different time.

671
01:00:05.070 --> 01:00:08.020
The airbenders were the
peacekeepers of the four elements.

672
01:00:08.670 --> 01:00:13.020
We used our power to mediate
all conflict with nonviolence.

673
01:00:13.170 --> 01:00:16.020
But we were the fewest in numbers.

674
01:00:16.021 --> 01:00:21.020
For many years. we existed in a
beautiful balance of great prosperity.

675
01:00:21.420 --> 01:00:24.020
But the world began to shift.

676
01:00:24.021 --> 01:00:29.020
The earthbenders formed their own kingdom.
separating from the other elemental tribes.

677
01:00:29.220 --> 01:00:32.020
The balance of the world was at risk.

678
01:00:32.220 --> 01:00:35.020
It was my duty to act.

679
01:00:35.021 --> 01:00:37.594
So I learned how to
channel the energy of the

680
01:00:37.606 --> 01:00:40.020
spirit world just as
the lion turtles did.

681
01:00:40.270 --> 01:00:44.020
To give people the power of airbending.

682
01:00:44.021 --> 01:00:49.020
My most devout pupil.
Tagah. was the first to receive it.

683
01:00:49.520 --> 01:00:54.020
I sent my new peacekeepers out
to help calm the growing unrest.

684
01:00:54.670 --> 01:01:01.020
But they were not prepared for the
brutality of the new earth kingdom.

685
01:01:01.021 --> 01:01:07.020
Tagah watched as his brothers
and sisters were all slaughtered.

686
01:01:07.695 --> 01:01:10.020
His heart darkened by the violence of war.

687
01:01:10.695 --> 01:01:16.020
He now saw everyone who
wasn't an air nomad as the enemy.

688
01:01:16.220 --> 01:01:18.663
Tagah begged me to
use the staff to create an

689
01:01:18.675 --> 01:01:21.020
army and to kill all
who would do us harm.

690
01:01:21.021 --> 01:01:23.020
I refused.

691
01:01:23.571 --> 01:01:26.020
So he stole it.

692
01:01:26.021 --> 01:01:28.422
When he connected
the staff to the temple.

693
01:01:28.434 --> 01:01:31.020
his energy was so
corrupted by grief and rage

694
01:01:31.021 --> 01:01:35.020
that the power of the
spirit world consumed him.

695
01:01:35.021 --> 01:01:41.020
Tagah became something more
than human. too powerful to kill.

696
01:01:41.021 --> 01:01:44.233
It took all my energy
to finally trap him high

697
01:01:44.258 --> 01:01:47.546
high above the clouds and
no one would find him.

698
01:01:48.470 --> 01:01:53.020
I reclaimed the staff.
but I was fatally wounded.

699
01:01:53.270 --> 01:01:56.073
Before the earth kingdom
could invade Jurana. I

700
01:01:56.085 --> 01:01:59.020
sent the remaining air
nomads into the mountains.

701
01:01:59.120 --> 01:02:04.347
And I hid my temple in the spirit world
where no one could access its power.

702
01:02:06.170 --> 01:02:12.020
Then I locked the staff away
where only the avatar could find it.

703
01:02:12.021 --> 01:02:16.162
I died hoping that one day
another avatar would create

704
01:02:16.174 --> 01:02:20.020
more airbenders and
restore balance to this world.

705
01:02:20.295 --> 01:02:23.020
And that avatar is you. Aang.

706
01:02:23.420 --> 01:02:27.020
You have to get my staff before
Tagah connects it to the temple.

707
01:02:27.470 --> 01:02:31.020
There's still time.
Don't let my regret become yours.

708
01:02:31.820 --> 01:02:34.020
My friends and I fought
hard for this peace.

709
01:02:34.870 --> 01:02:37.020
I won't let him start another war.

710
01:02:37.021 --> 01:02:40.020
Help me find a way back.

711
01:02:40.021 --> 01:02:42.020
Sonam?

712
01:02:43.070 --> 01:02:44.906
What's happening?

713
01:02:46.284 --> 01:02:50.020
No! No! Please! I have to fix this!

714
01:02:50.021 --> 01:02:55.020
This can't be it! I can't die yet!
Please! Not yet! No!

715
01:02:55.021 --> 01:02:57.020
- Aang? - Katara?

716
01:02:57.021 --> 01:03:04.020
Come on. Aang! Come on!
Aang! Move up! Aang!

717
01:03:04.770 --> 01:03:07.020
- Katara. - I was so worried.

718
01:03:07.220 --> 01:03:12.020
Aang. Sokka.
I knew you'd pull through. buddy.

719
01:03:12.470 --> 01:03:14.020
- Hey. Aang. - Zuko.

720
01:03:14.420 --> 01:03:18.020
- Momo. - Welcome back. Twinkle Toes.

721
01:03:18.170 --> 01:03:23.020
Toph. you're okay.
I thought you were all dead.

722
01:03:23.021 --> 01:03:26.020
We were. but Katara saved us.

723
01:03:26.470 --> 01:03:32.020
The spiritual power of these waters
strengthened my healing abilities.

724
01:03:33.176 --> 01:03:36.020
You're incredible. Katara.

725
01:03:36.731 --> 01:03:38.731
Where's Appa?

726
01:03:39.470 --> 01:03:41.020
Tagah must have taken him.

727
01:03:41.945 --> 01:03:43.020
I'm sorry.

728
01:03:43.370 --> 01:03:45.020
No.

729
01:03:45.820 --> 01:03:49.020
I can't believe I trusted him.

730
01:03:49.720 --> 01:03:52.020
We'll get through this.

731
01:03:53.992 --> 01:03:55.152
So. let me get this straight.

732
01:03:55.970 --> 01:04:00.020
He's pulling Sonam's temple out of
the spirit world to gain unlimited power?

733
01:04:00.021 --> 01:04:03.020
And let me guess. you want us to stop him?

734
01:04:04.020 --> 01:04:09.020
Sure. Only problem is your air bro
crushed our ship and stole your bison.

735
01:04:09.220 --> 01:04:13.020
Also. there's a massive
typhoon surrounding us!

736
01:04:14.903 --> 01:04:18.903
I don't say this very
often. but Sokka's right.

737
01:04:18.948 --> 01:04:21.020
- Thank you. - Yep. we're stuck.

738
01:04:21.220 --> 01:04:24.020
And there aren't enough lion turtles
for all of us to have our own island.

739
01:04:24.021 --> 01:04:27.020
So. I'm calling this one.
I'm naming him Snappy.

740
01:04:27.070 --> 01:04:31.020
- Aw. Snappy is the best one. - I know.

741
01:04:31.220 --> 01:04:34.008
We may not know where
Tagah is. but we know

742
01:04:34.020 --> 01:04:37.020
what he's looking for
is in the spirit world.

743
01:04:37.445 --> 01:04:42.020
And lucky for us. we're stuck in the most
spiritually charged place on the planet.

744
01:04:42.770 --> 01:04:49.020
So. I may be able to open a portal to get
us there. if I can summon an old friend.

745
01:04:57.309 --> 01:05:00.020
Wow. The ocean spirit.

746
01:05:08.771 --> 01:05:11.020
This portal smells an
awful lot like the fish market.

747
01:05:11.021 --> 01:05:13.020
I'm gonna go check on Snappy.

748
01:05:13.170 --> 01:05:15.020
Face your death with honor.

749
01:05:15.070 --> 01:05:20.020
I'm sorry. I know I got us into
this. but I promise you I'll fix it.

750
01:05:20.021 --> 01:05:22.020
We'll fix it.

751
01:05:22.021 --> 01:05:24.020
Together.

752
01:05:27.376 --> 01:05:30.020
We're gonna die! We're gonna die!

753
01:05:39.953 --> 01:05:42.045
What? Where's my power pony?

754
01:05:42.998 --> 01:05:45.020
Were my hands always this small?

755
01:05:45.021 --> 01:05:48.020
It's baby Toph! Baby Toph!

756
01:05:49.270 --> 01:05:51.020
What the hog monkey?

757
01:05:51.021 --> 01:05:53.020
Old people!
Grand Grand?

758
01:05:53.021 --> 01:05:55.020
That's your sister. you weak head!

759
01:05:55.021 --> 01:05:58.020
Give me Toph. There. there. Toph.

760
01:05:58.021 --> 01:06:01.020
Oh no. Zuko!
What happened to your beautiful face?

761
01:06:01.021 --> 01:06:03.020
You look like a dried sea squid.

762
01:06:03.070 --> 01:06:05.020
Ugh tired.
No. Zuko!

763
01:06:05.021 --> 01:06:07.020
What's going on here?

764
01:06:07.021 --> 01:06:11.020
The spirit world is out of balance.

765
01:06:11.970 --> 01:06:13.020
And so are we.

766
01:06:15.109 --> 01:06:18.007
That's gotta be Tagah.

767
01:06:38.182 --> 01:06:39.468
Oh no!

768
01:06:39.469 --> 01:06:42.020
He's pulling Sonim's
temple into our world!

769
01:06:42.021 --> 01:06:44.020
We're running out of time!

770
01:06:51.710 --> 01:06:53.709
Pretty good landing.

771
01:06:54.020 --> 01:06:57.020
Whoa! Humans! I love humans!

772
01:06:57.245 --> 01:07:00.020
Two brothers. their little
sister. and an elderly couple.

773
01:07:00.170 --> 01:07:02.020
Not a couple!

774
01:07:02.021 --> 01:07:04.020
Whoa! Looks like I touched a nerve.

775
01:07:04.120 --> 01:07:07.020
Oh. look at this one! Hello!

776
01:07:07.021 --> 01:07:09.020
Toph! No! Bad Toph!

777
01:07:09.021 --> 01:07:11.020
We don't bite strangers.

778
01:07:12.020 --> 01:07:16.020
Great spirit! Excuse me. did you
just come from that temple in the sky?

779
01:07:16.021 --> 01:07:18.020
I certainly did.

780
01:07:18.021 --> 01:07:20.020
It was my favorite hidey hole.

781
01:07:20.021 --> 01:07:23.020
Until that dark. yucky energy
started corrupting this whole place.

782
01:07:23.021 --> 01:07:27.020
Please. we need your help getting up there.

783
01:07:27.021 --> 01:07:29.020
It's my duty to stop this.

784
01:07:29.220 --> 01:07:31.020
I'm the Avatar.

785
01:07:31.270 --> 01:07:35.020
Ooh! The Avatar!

786
01:07:35.120 --> 01:07:37.020
Let me have a squiz at you.

787
01:07:37.170 --> 01:07:39.020
Okay. now with this eye.

788
01:07:39.021 --> 01:07:42.020
And this eye.
Ooh. don't forget this eye.

789
01:07:42.021 --> 01:07:44.020
Can we hurry it up?
I need to have a squiz.

790
01:07:44.021 --> 01:07:46.020
Sniff check!

791
01:07:47.444 --> 01:07:50.020
Ooh. that's Avatar material right there.

792
01:07:50.021 --> 01:07:53.020
Yes. it is. Oh!
Yes. yes. yes. yes. yes!

793
01:07:53.021 --> 01:07:58.020
It appears the universe has brought
us together for a very important mission.

794
01:08:00.687 --> 01:08:02.020
To flee!

795
01:08:02.021 --> 01:08:04.020
And be alive!

796
01:08:04.045 --> 01:08:05.243
Wait! Come back!

797
01:08:05.531 --> 01:08:06.996
We're going the wrong way!

798
01:08:07.065 --> 01:08:10.020
Stop! Please. great spirit.
both of our worlds are in danger.

799
01:08:10.021 --> 01:08:13.020
No. no. no. no. no. no.
I am not going back up there.

800
01:08:19.303 --> 01:08:21.996
Hmm. well. when you put it like
that. it does make more sense.

801
01:08:23.748 --> 01:08:27.020
Upon reflection. I've decided I shall
help you and your human-y friends.

802
01:08:27.021 --> 01:08:29.020
What did he say?

803
01:08:29.021 --> 01:08:32.020
Nice work. mama.
Alright. in you go.

804
01:08:35.020 --> 01:08:38.260
By the way. no eating anything you find
in my teeth. as I'm saving that for later.

805
01:08:38.605 --> 01:08:41.020
Ready. set. get steady and rest.

806
01:08:41.021 --> 01:08:44.020
One and the two and
the you know what to do.

807
01:08:44.021 --> 01:08:45.205
Bluff!

808
01:08:50.392 --> 01:08:54.770
I know we haven't known each
other very long. but I love you!

809
01:08:54.814 --> 01:08:56.020
You don't have to say it back.

810
01:09:05.020 --> 01:09:07.020
Hey! You got your hair back!

811
01:09:07.045 --> 01:09:09.365
Why are my eyes cheery? Was I crying?

812
01:09:10.120 --> 01:09:12.020
No way! Look!

813
01:09:12.395 --> 01:09:14.020
What? What is it?

814
01:09:14.021 --> 01:09:16.020
It's Republic City.

815
01:09:19.208 --> 01:09:22.020
We can't let him destroy
everything we've built.

816
01:09:22.021 --> 01:09:23.452
We won't.

817
01:09:38.953 --> 01:09:40.308
Boomerang!

818
01:09:56.964 --> 01:09:59.020
Give me the staff. Tagah!

819
01:09:59.021 --> 01:10:01.608
I see I underestimated you. Avatar.

820
01:10:01.875 --> 01:10:04.020
Your friends are stronger than I thought.

821
01:10:04.021 --> 01:10:06.020
But you're too late.

822
01:10:13.719 --> 01:10:15.020
The Denied.

823
01:10:15.070 --> 01:10:18.020
You see. I did what you wanted. Aang.

824
01:10:18.021 --> 01:10:21.020
I returned airbending to the world.

825
01:10:23.074 --> 01:10:24.270
What's the plan?

826
01:10:24.295 --> 01:10:27.020
We'll deal with the Denied.
You have to get the staff.

827
01:10:27.620 --> 01:10:32.846
I will rebuild Jurana and the ruins
of our enemies. just as they did on ours.

828
01:10:32.871 --> 01:10:37.020
A new air empire will rise. Kill them all.

829
01:10:55.333 --> 01:10:58.020
We have to get these people out of here.

830
01:11:02.020 --> 01:11:04.020
Whoa!

831
01:11:13.955 --> 01:11:15.555
Oh. yeah.

832
01:11:22.799 --> 01:11:25.162
Tagah! Give it to me!

833
01:11:26.873 --> 01:11:32.020
This isn't the way. We can use the
staff to bring back the balance. Peace!

834
01:11:32.021 --> 01:11:36.020
You care so much about your
ideals that you'd let your people die!

835
01:11:36.731 --> 01:11:40.200
I will do anything to
make sure they survive!

836
01:11:57.021 --> 01:12:01.020
My cabbages! My cabbages!

837
01:12:05.981 --> 01:12:11.020
My cabbages! My cabbages!

838
01:12:23.581 --> 01:12:25.020
Don't do this.

839
01:12:25.286 --> 01:12:28.020
You have the power now.
You can decide how to use it.

840
01:12:28.245 --> 01:12:31.020
I'm not like you.
The world hasn't been good to me.

841
01:12:31.021 --> 01:12:33.020
The world is what we make it.

842
01:12:33.021 --> 01:12:34.837
Get away from her!

843
01:13:06.142 --> 01:13:07.830
Tagah! Stop!

844
01:13:12.875 --> 01:13:15.020
You betrayed me! You betrayed our culture!

845
01:13:15.021 --> 01:13:18.020
I gave you every chance to see the truth!

846
01:13:22.749 --> 01:13:25.996
Can you be in the Fire Nation?

847
01:13:27.416 --> 01:13:30.020
I'm fighting for the peace of all nations.

848
01:13:34.016 --> 01:13:38.020
Big talk from someone who sits
on a throne built on a century of war!

849
01:14:00.708 --> 01:14:04.321
I'm still the greatest
earthbender in the world!

850
01:14:27.711 --> 01:14:30.020
Oh no! I'm out of water!

851
01:14:33.310 --> 01:14:34.730
We got ya!

852
01:14:34.755 --> 01:14:37.020
And there's no Avatar here to save you.

853
01:14:39.046 --> 01:14:41.020
Sokka cycle!

854
01:14:44.735 --> 01:14:49.020
Let's see if your fancy new bending can
beat some good ol' non-bending know-how!

855
01:14:55.696 --> 01:14:57.496
Bombs away!

856
01:15:04.474 --> 01:15:06.020
You just got denied!

857
01:15:14.185 --> 01:15:17.020
Let's go!
Good luck saving your city!

858
01:15:26.196 --> 01:15:29.303
We have to save as many people as we can!

859
01:15:46.503 --> 01:15:51.407
I know your pain.
I know what you've been through.

860
01:15:51.432 --> 01:15:53.020
You don't know.

861
01:15:53.370 --> 01:15:57.020
I watched as all of my brothers
and sisters were slaughtered.

862
01:15:57.021 --> 01:16:01.957
And the Fire Nation burned
the Air Nomads to ash!

863
01:16:02.090 --> 01:16:04.218
Where were you?

864
01:16:04.243 --> 01:16:05.446
You ran!

865
01:16:26.347 --> 01:16:28.308
Tagah!

866
01:16:37.633 --> 01:16:39.239
No!

867
01:17:00.974 --> 01:17:07.578
The full power of the Spirit
World flows through me!

868
01:17:15.889 --> 01:17:19.020
This is what strength looks like!

869
01:18:10.883 --> 01:18:17.605
You should've run away like you
did all those years ago. little Avatar.

870
01:18:17.961 --> 01:18:22.020
I... won't... run.

871
01:18:22.021 --> 01:18:26.020
Then at least you'll die knowing
you're not the last Airbender!

872
01:19:02.646 --> 01:19:04.114
Aang!

873
01:19:12.214 --> 01:19:13.792
No!

874
01:20:20.433 --> 01:20:25.519
We could've been brothers!
We could've done this together!

875
01:20:25.544 --> 01:20:27.543
It didn't have to end like this!

876
01:20:32.473 --> 01:20:34.574
It's Aang. He's got the staff!

877
01:20:34.599 --> 01:20:36.598
Yeah! Kick his butt. Mega Aang!

878
01:20:36.623 --> 01:20:40.622
No! Something's wrong!
The power is corrupting him!

879
01:20:47.969 --> 01:20:50.020
Ahh!

880
01:20:58.592 --> 01:21:02.827
I dreamt of bringing the Air Nomads
back to the world as peacekeepers.

881
01:21:02.852 --> 01:21:06.020
They could've been a beacon
of light for the world to follow.

882
01:21:06.021 --> 01:21:10.822
But you ruined it!
You twisted my grave into a nightmare!

883
01:21:10.847 --> 01:21:14.800
Finally.
You have the power the Air Nomads need.

884
01:21:14.825 --> 01:21:17.020
Maybe there is hope for you after all.

885
01:21:27.705 --> 01:21:34.240
Do it! Use the staff! Show me you have
the strength to bring our people back!

886
01:21:34.265 --> 01:21:35.327
Do it!

887
01:22:12.220 --> 01:22:13.220
Aang...

888
01:22:16.070 --> 01:22:19.792
You will do so many
great things as the Avatar.

889
01:22:19.970 --> 01:22:24.437
But you must be prepared to
do what frightens you the most.

890
01:22:25.237 --> 01:22:30.020
Your people. your home.
we are always with you.

891
01:22:46.664 --> 01:22:47.664
No!

892
01:22:53.370 --> 01:22:55.220
No!

893
01:23:18.464 --> 01:23:20.976
No! My power!

894
01:23:27.318 --> 01:23:30.119
No. No!

895
01:23:39.420 --> 01:23:45.167
You fool! Why? Why did you break it?

896
01:23:45.301 --> 01:23:48.612
We could've fixed everything.

897
01:23:48.901 --> 01:23:51.020
We can't erase the pain of the past.

898
01:23:52.511 --> 01:23:54.008
We couldn't save them.

899
01:23:54.033 --> 01:23:58.147
But it's our duty to protect our people.

900
01:23:58.172 --> 01:24:01.460
Not at the cost of betraying
everything they stood for.

901
01:24:01.485 --> 01:24:03.347
No.

902
01:24:03.372 --> 01:24:05.994
It's time to let go.

903
01:24:06.019 --> 01:24:08.328
You have to forgive yourself.

904
01:24:10.320 --> 01:24:12.020
I have to forgive myself too.

905
01:24:21.420 --> 01:24:24.020
Air Nomads are formed from the best.

906
01:24:28.355 --> 01:24:32.020
We walk the world for a moment in time.

907
01:24:34.435 --> 01:24:39.020
Then we return to the eternal wind.

908
01:24:54.617 --> 01:24:56.020
Aang!

909
01:24:59.816 --> 01:25:01.694
Hey. Katara.

910
01:25:01.920 --> 01:25:03.020
Hey. Aang.

911
01:25:05.020 --> 01:25:06.020
Seriously?

912
01:25:06.021 --> 01:25:09.020
You do realize you're falling. right?

913
01:25:09.520 --> 01:25:11.020
Hey. if you ever get
tired of relying on Appa.

914
01:25:11.021 --> 01:25:13.020
I can hook you up with
one of these babies.

915
01:25:18.439 --> 01:25:21.152
I'll give you the best friend discount!

916
01:25:35.120 --> 01:25:37.020
I don't know if
airbending will ever return.

917
01:25:38.170 --> 01:25:41.020
But I know now that the
true power of the Air Nomads

918
01:25:41.820 --> 01:25:43.020
was never their bending.

919
01:25:43.570 --> 01:25:45.020
It was their values.

920
01:25:45.720 --> 01:25:48.020
And that's a power I can pass on to others.

921
01:25:49.320 --> 01:25:54.020
Avatar Aang. you are the true
embodiment of the Air Nomads.

922
01:25:55.220 --> 01:25:58.020
Thank you for giving up
the power that I could not.

923
01:25:59.395 --> 01:26:02.020
You give me hope for
the future of our culture.

924
01:26:16.008 --> 01:26:18.020
It's amazing. isn't it?

925
01:26:18.570 --> 01:26:22.276
The first new air temple in centuries.

926
01:26:22.683 --> 01:26:25.020
Republic City is finally complete.

927
01:26:29.283 --> 01:26:32.794
A city for all nations.
just like you promised.

928
01:26:33.770 --> 01:26:36.020
I never could have done
this without you. Katara.

929
01:26:37.720 --> 01:26:40.020
Hey. everybody.
Sorry I kept you all waiting.

930
01:26:40.720 --> 01:26:42.020
Are you ready for our big trip?

931
01:26:43.070 --> 01:26:45.020
As my new acolytes.

932
01:26:45.220 --> 01:26:49.020
you'll be helping me preserve
our culture for future generations.

933
01:26:49.070 --> 01:26:54.020
So. who wants to search for artifacts
at an ancient abandoned temple?

934
01:26:54.021 --> 01:26:55.195
Yay.

935
01:26:55.220 --> 01:26:59.020
I'm only going to make sure you don't
try to release another beefy old airbender.

936
01:26:59.021 --> 01:27:01.020
Yeah. I'm done with bad boys.

937
01:27:13.463 --> 01:27:16.020
Avatar Sonam told me about this place.

938
01:27:16.270 --> 01:27:20.020
so it's very possible that no one's
been here in hundreds of years.

939
01:27:21.420 --> 01:27:24.020
Oh. is this an airbender relic?

940
01:27:24.295 --> 01:27:26.020
I think that's just a rock.

941
01:27:26.070 --> 01:27:28.020
But I love the enthusiasm.

942
01:27:29.447 --> 01:27:30.533
Oh.

943
01:27:33.820 --> 01:27:35.020
Keep your eyes open.

944
01:27:35.320 --> 01:27:37.040
You never know what we might discover here.

945
01:27:38.264 --> 01:27:39.864
Oh.

946
01:27:46.737 --> 01:27:48.670
I thought they were extinct.

947
01:27:55.426 --> 01:27:57.020
I can't believe it.

948
01:27:57.021 --> 01:27:59.020
The original airbenders.

949
01:28:06.021 --> 01:28:09.020
Oh. can I have one?

950
01:28:10.021 --> 01:28:12.020
Appa. yip yip!

951
01:28:24.722 --> 01:28:40.356
Proper subs by [mlnl]

